## Providers

A provider connects your application to an Ethereum node, handling the underlying protocol and providing methods to send transactions, retrieve balances, and query contract data.

#### JsonRpcProvider

A straightforward way to interact with Ethereum nodes for querying balances and other operations.

```typescript
import { JsonRpcProvider } from 'essential-eth';

const provider = new JsonRpcProvider();
await provider
  .getBalance('0x7cB57B5A97eAbe94205C07890BE4c1aD31E486A8')
  .then((balance) => console.log(balance.toString()));
// returns: "28798127851528138"
```

#### FallthroughProvider

Designed for reliability -- automatically switches to the next URL if a node fails to respond.

```typescript
import { FallthroughProvider } from 'essential-eth';

const provider = new FallthroughProvider([
  'https://bad.com',
  'https://free-eth-node.com/api/eth',
]);
provider.getGasPrice().toNumber();
// returns: 39695942769
```

